race.comment: TREASURER (2) dropped in grade and returned to form last start, working home powerfully to be beaten just 0.4 lengths over a similar trip to this at Beaudesert. That was his first try at the mile so he should take a lot from the run. Ready to win again. BRIGHT THE SUN (11) settled a long way back and only made minimal ground in the run home when resuming over 1350m at this track last time out. Has raced once over today's distance for a win so watch for a far better performance. ARTSPACE (3) failed over 1800m at Eagle Farm recently in a run worth overlooking. Beaten just a length over 1600m at the Sunshine Coast two back which is a better guide to his chances. GOT YOURSELF A GUN (5) overcame a poor start to work home for a close fourth over 1550m at Murwillumbah last start. Gets a soft run from gate one and should be competitive. Last start Gatton winner CLEARLY GEORGE (4) is worth an each-way ticket.
